<h2 id="handling-free-checkout">Handling Free Checkout <a class="headerlink" href="free-checkout#handling-free-checkout" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>But that's not <em>quite</em> everything we need to do. Thanks to the discount, Stripe
will already know that it doesn't need to charge the user, and so, the customer
doesn't need to have a card. But, the funny thing is, up until now, our <code>OrderController</code>
logic is expecting a <code>stripeToken</code> to <em>always</em> be submitted:</p>
