<h2 id="optionally-apply-the-stripe-token">Optionally Apply the Stripe Token <a class="headerlink" href="free-checkout#optionally-apply-the-stripe-token" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>But now, our code needs to be smart enough to <em>not</em> try to attach the token to the
Customer for free orders. At the top, add a <em>sanity</em> check: if there is <em>no</em> token,
and the shopping cart's total with discount is <em>not</em> free... well, we have a problem!
Throw a clear exception: the order is non-free... but we're missing the payment token!</p>
