<p>Ok, we're done! A free checkout and a normal checkout are <em>almost</em> the same. The only
difference is that you <em>don't</em> have a Stripe token, so you can't attach that to your
Customer.</p>
<p>Refresh the checkout page and, "Checkout for Free".</p>
<p>It works! In Stripe, find our Customer. There is no new payment, but there <em>is</em> an
Invoice for $0 and an active subscription. The Invoice shows off the discount.</p>
<h2 id="no-card-webhook-problems">No Card? Webhook Problems <a class="headerlink" href="free-checkout#no-card-webhook-problems" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Thanks to this change, it's now possible for a Customer to <em>not</em> have <em>any</em> cards
attached in Stripe. And yea know what? This creates a new problem in a <em>totally</em>
unrelated part of the process: webhooks.</p>
<p>But, it's no big deal. Open <code>WebhookController</code> and find the <code>invoice.payment_failed</code>
section. Wait! Woh! Before that - oh geez - fix my <em>horrible</em> typo: <code>invoice.payment_succeeded</code>:</p>
